Name: Versailles
Phrase: -Tch!
--Remember this, Divine Children of the Iridescent Clouds.
--Stay out of the clouds and the dusk.\n--Do not approach the darkness of the night or the darkness of the dawn.\n--Do not touch the Guardians of the Giant Trees.
--Remember my words.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: The Nacht is over...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Does this mean that the monster has left here?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: There is no sign of the mysterious Phantom Mist anymore. Look. The Metro Hole is right there!

Name: Versailles
Phrase: The brightness of the celestial sphere is almost the same as at standard time. The anomalies that were occurring in this area seem to have subsided.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Versailles, we did it.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Oui, we did.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: We saved M. St. Iris, no, Iris Metro! We did it, Miyako! The Allied Forces have won!
The Phantom Mist around the Metro Hole disappeared. The Nacht under the upper celestial spheres also returned to normal behaviour.

The presence of a mysterious being who calls himself the "King of Ever-Darkness", is a powerful enemy that has never been seen or felt in Iris Cloud. This cannot be overlooked and will have to be dealt with moving on, as a problem to both Iris Cloud and Iris Metro.
-Do not touch the Guardians of the Giant Trees.
That is not possible. In order to clear the Sea of Fog in Iris Cloud, and to prevent the influx of the Poison that plagues the Giant Tree, we had to meet the Guardians of the Giant Trees.

Name: Islington
Phrase: Now theeen~ now that we know we'll be able to return to Iris Cloud safely. We'll leave as soon as we caaan~

Name: Islington
Phrase: ...Having said that~

Name: M. St. Irish Citizen
Phrase: Lady Islington~! Please! Please stay here and save the Metro world!

Name: M. St. Irish Citizen
Phrase: Please teach the secret arts of Iris Cloud to the Divine Children of Iris Metro!

Name: M. St. Irish Male Citizen
Phrase: Lady Islington! I love you! I, I've become your fan~!

Name: Mary
Phrase: You're very popular here. Considered becoming a Divine Child over here?

Name: Islington
Phrase: Hmmm~ seems my charisma is universal.

Name: Mary
Phrase: Seems like the Metro's Divine Children don't have special powers. The Metro Hole that they used as an altar was opened now. There's a big fuss about it since Conductor and Islington descended here.

Name: Islington
Phrase: That Metro Hole they used as an altar instead is in the Royal Castle, isn't it? Looking on the map of Iris Cloud, there's a stop for a Mist Train stop... Perhaps?

Name: Mary
Phrase: There's a good chance they're connected. If they were, it would make it easier to go up and down, wouldn't it?

Name: Islington
Phrase: I think we should take it easy. I think we should go back the way we came.

Name: Mary
Phrase: How can you be absolutely sure it's safe?

Name: Mary
Phrase: 'And the Divine Children over here, 'The Metro Hole is the link between Iris Cloud and Iris Metro.' That's what they say in the old texts.

Name: Islington
Phrase: Well, yeah.

Name: Mary
Phrase: Now, wouldn't it be easier to stay here at the royal castle then?

Name: Islington
Phrase: Ugh...

Name: Islington
Phrase: Absolutely no! We'll go back to our universe through the Metro Hole outside! We'll find out if we can use the other one, when we get back to Iris Cloud!

Name: Mary
Phrase: You're surprisingly cautious. Divine Children should be more than a little mischievous, don't you think?

Name: Islington
Phrase: Oh, shaddap! Don't get me started on Riccardo Trevithick!

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miss Queensway, thank you so much for your help this time.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: No, I did what a knight should do.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I hear the Metro Hole in our Royal Castle has been opened. We hope that this will allow us to coordinate with the SSS.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: I'm sure we will be able to. We may one day ask Miss Versailles and the others to help us too. We would be grateful for your help then.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Of course! We will do our best to cooperate with you.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: But we still have a lot of work to do here...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Conductor told me about it. A mysterious structure has appeared near the Giant Tree.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Oui. There's a giant castle within the Mist.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: A castle? That sounds like another tough mission. We've had iron ruins appear out of nowhere in the woods on our world. I'm sure it'll disappear once we hit the source, but... be careful.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Oui. Miyako and I will go to the Metro Hole to investigate. If we can't get to the bottom of it, then you all can come over to help.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Then you should bring a bigger group.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Non, we will go alone. In the first place, it's not safe to go to and from the Metro Hole on foot...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: ...I know, I know. I'm sorry, that was irresponsible of me.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Sir Conductor said that we will build a base for the SSS in Metro as well, if we can get permission from upper management. Sir said that he and Lady Islington would persuade the Allied Forces to do so.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: So wait for us. We'll have the Mist Train run up to you.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Alright. We will wait in anticipation.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: See you later, then, Yoshino-chan.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes, be well, Miyako.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Before we say goodbye, may Yoshino ask you a few questions?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes, that would be great.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: What are your hobbies?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Hobbies?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Umm, sewing doll's kimonos? It's not really a hobby, but that's what I used to do before I joined the army.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Ooooh- doll seamstress.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Ooooh-...

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yoshino-chan? What's wrong? Do you have a stomachache?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: No, Yoshino's fine. Just a little bit happy, so happy, Yoshino can't really put it into words.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino is a seamstress too, but not for dolls, Yoshino makes kimonos for people to wear.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I see. Then you're just like me.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes, that's right. Next time, will you teach Yoshino how to make a small kimono?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Of course. Maybe next time we meet.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes... next time.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: See you next time. Yoshino will come on the train with you all.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes! See you again!
Thus, Versailles and Miyako, who had came from the subterranean world, returned to where they had been.
The Special Steel Squad then, thanks to Islington's prudent judgement, went back the way they came through that Metro Hole again and returned to Iris Cloud.
Subsequent investigations revealed that the Metro is also connected to the Metro Hole in the Royal Castle. In response, the Iris Cloud Allied Forces decided to investigate into Iris Metro.
-A subterranean world with many celestial spheres hanging from the ceiling.
Where does the railway of Iris Metro really lead to?
